h) Procedures for responding to requests for disclosure, etc.
To request notification of the purpose of use, disclosure, correction, addition or deletion, suspension of use, elimination, suspension of provision to third parties, or disclosure of records of provision to third parties (collectively, "Disclosure, etc.") of retained personal data, please contact our "Contact for complaints regarding handling of retained personal data" listed above. Please contact the "Contact for complaints regarding the handling of retained personal data". Please fill in the necessary items on the "Application Form" and attach documents that confirm the applicant's identity. (For example, a copy of your driver's license, passport, health insurance card, pension book, residence card, special permanent resident certificate, or my number card (front side only) with or without a photo. (1 point for each of the two types if they do not have a photograph). In the case of a request for disclosure, etc. by a representative, a document that verifies the identity of the principal, a letter of attorney from the principal, and a copy of a document that verifies the identity of the representative must be submitted. In the case of a request for disclosure, etc. by a legal representative, a document that can verify the identity of the principal, a copy of a document that can prove the identity of the legal representative (certificate of registered matters, etc., or in the case of a person with parental authority, a copy of the family register, extract from the family register, certified copy of resident registration or other document that can prove the relationship with the principal) and a document that can verify the identity of the representative must be submitted.
A fee of 1,000 yen per request will be charged for notification or disclosure of the purpose of use of personal data or disclosure of records of provision of personal data to a third party. (Please enclose a postal money order with your request form, etc.)
